♪ I know I can make it ♪

44
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:53,697
♪ I know I can make it through ♪

45
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:01,205
MANNY.

46
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:03,123
PIE CHARTS?

47
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:04,291
WE'VE DONE PIE CHARTS
EVERY YEAR

48
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:05,292
SINCE GRADE FOUR.

49
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:06,168
IT'S A CHORE WHEEL.

50
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:09,338
MANNY:
(SIGHS) OKAY, DOES IT
HAVE LAUNDRY ON IT?

51
00:02:09,421 --> 00:02:10,506
BECAUSE I'M OUT
OF UNDERWEAR

52
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:14,426
AND THIS COMMANDO CHAFING
IS KILLING ME.

53
00:02:15,511 --> 00:02:18,514
NOT UP TO YOUR USUAL
STANDARD.

54
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:26,355
OKAY,
MANNY YOU ARE ON LAUNDRY.

55
00:02:26,438 --> 00:02:27,606
I'M ON HOMEWORK

56
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:28,565
AND EXERCISE

57
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:30,943
AND GROCERY SHOPPING
AND CLEANING

58
00:02:31,026 --> 00:02:32,819
AND MOM MANAGEMENT.

59
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:34,821
THAT SHOULD BURN
A FEW CALORIES.

60
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:36,823
I SINCERELY HOPE SO.

61
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:38,534
YOU'RE A STICK,
AND YOU'RE INSANE.

62
00:02:44,206 --> 00:02:45,374
MOM! I'M HOME!

63
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,668
MANNY:
SHE'S WORKING LATE.

64
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:48,836
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

65
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:50,003
BABY PEDICURE?

66
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:53,340
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH FAT
IS IN ONE CHIP?

67
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:54,758
I BROUGHT YOU CELERY.

68
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,134
CELERY HAS NEGATIVE CALORIES

69
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:59,096
BECAUSE YOU BURN CALORIES
WHILE YOU'RE CHEWING.

70
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:00,430
AND THIS...

71
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:03,976
I AM NOT EATING PAPER.

72
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:06,478
NO MATTER HOW MANY
CALORIES IT BURNS.

73
00:03:06,562 --> 00:03:07,855
IT'S A DIET DIARY.

74
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:09,940
WE MARK DOWN EVERY MORSEL
THAT GOES INTO OUR MOUTHS.

75
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:12,234
GREAT.
MORE HOMEWORK.

76
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:14,653
DO YOU WANT TO GET
THIS AGENT?

77
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:17,489
THINK OF IT AS FUN.

78
00:03:17,573 --> 00:03:19,074
THINK OF IT
AS A CHALLENGE.

79
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:21,785
(UNENTHUSIASTIC) WOO-HOO,
LET THE FUN BEGIN.

80
00:03:22,578 --> 00:03:23,996
(BACHMAN TURNER OVERDRIVE
PLAYING)

81
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:28,792
♪♪♪

82
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:33,297
♪ 'CAUSE YOU AIN'T
SEEN NOTHIN YET ♪

83
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:37,050
♪ B-B-BABY, NO,
YOU AIN'T SEEN NOTHIN YET ♪

84
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:40,846
WITH A VOICE LIKE THAT?

85
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,056
IT'S NO WONDER "THE ZITS"
NEVER WENT ANYWHERE.

86
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,892
DIANE AND SIMPSON:
OHHH!

87
00:03:44,975 --> 00:03:47,186
I'VE HEARD HIM SING
IN THE SHOWER, SNAKE?

88
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:48,812
AND THE POT
SHOULD REALLY STOP

89
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,147
CALLING THE KETTLE BLACK.

90
00:03:50,606 --> 00:03:51,607
SAUCY...

91
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:54,151
BUT A KEEPER.

92
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:00,324
ALL RIGHT,

93
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,242
LET'S KEEP THIS
PARTY GOING.

94
00:04:02,326 --> 00:04:04,203
I'VE GOT JUST THE NUMBER.

95
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:07,164
IT'S A CLASSIC LITTLE DITTY
I LIKE TO CALL

96
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,665
"ROCK THE CASBAH".

97
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:10,167
(GIGGLES)
(ENGLISH ACCENT)
OY! KICK IT, MATE!

98
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:14,254
("SOMETIMES WHEN WE TOUCH"
PLAYS)

99
00:04:14,338 --> 00:04:15,589
WHAT?

100
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:16,924
I DIDN'T...

101
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:23,055
THAT'S "SOMETIMES
WHEN WE TOUCH".

102
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:24,806
(SOFT CHUCKLE)

103
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:26,642
ABORT! ABORT!

104
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:27,726
HEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

105
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:31,897
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

106
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,315
IT'S OUR SONG.

107
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:35,943
STUPID MACHINE.

108
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:36,902
SORRY SNAKE, UH...

109
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:40,781
BUTTONS GET MIXED UP
SOMETIMES.

110
00:04:40,864 --> 00:04:41,615
(MUSIC STOPS)

111
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:43,659
IT'S JUST THAT UH...

112
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:46,203
I MISS HER SO BAD,
YOU KNOW?

113
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,205
I MISS MY FAMILY.

114
00:04:59,883 --> 00:05:02,094
TOTAL CALORIES: 110.

115
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:03,720
TOTAL GRAMS OF FAT: 2.

116
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:05,389
TOTAL FLAVOUR: ZERO.

117
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:06,598
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO MATH

118
00:05:06,682 --> 00:05:08,892
WHEN I'M STARVING?

119
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,143
I THINK MY STOMACH'S
DIGESTING ITSELF.

120
00:05:10,227 --> 00:05:11,478
BUT WE ARE NOT
FEELING HUNGRY,

121
00:05:11,562 --> 00:05:12,479
WE ARE FEELING LIGHT.

122
00:05:12,563 --> 00:05:14,231
AS IN L-I-T-E?

123
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,277
OKAY, YOU NEED
TO JOG ONE MILE

124
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,319
AT SIX MILES AN HOUR

125
00:05:19,403 --> 00:05:22,030
TO BURN OFF
110 CALORIES.

126
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:25,450
OKAY, I'M GOING
TO GET A DIET POP

127
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:27,619
AND PRETEND
IT'S A MILKSHAKE.

128
00:05:27,703 --> 00:05:28,537
PAIGE:
OW!

129
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,834
UH... TWIGS AND BERRIES?

130
00:05:33,917 --> 00:05:36,211
YOU GIRLS PRACTICING
TO BE ON SURVIVOR?

131
00:05:36,295 --> 00:05:37,504
IT'S CALLED A DIET.

132
00:05:37,588 --> 00:05:40,007
MM... TOTALLY WISHING
I HAD YOUR WILLPOWER.

133
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:41,800
WHEN BATHING SUIT SEASON
COMES AROUND,

134
00:05:41,884 --> 00:05:43,427
PREPARE TO BE HATED
BY A JEALOUS ME.

135
00:05:47,973 --> 00:05:49,683
SUDDENLY I'M STUFFED.

136
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:52,186
(LAUGHS) WHEN ARE WE
RUNNING THAT MILE?

137
00:05:52,269 --> 00:05:54,188
OR FIVE? (LAUGHS)

138
00:05:54,897 --> 00:05:57,065
EMMA AND MANNY:
(LAUGHING)

139
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,568
BOTH:
(PANTING)

140
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:00,819
(LAUGHING)

141
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:03,197
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

142
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,616
NOTHING.
I JUST FEEL ALL... FLOATY.

143
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,159
(LAUGHING)

144
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:08,493
ME TOO.
IS THAT GOOD?

145
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:10,120
SOMEONE WANNA TELL ME
THE PUNCHLINE?

146
00:06:11,622 --> 00:06:12,956
SEE YOU INSIDE.

147
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:20,964
WHOA! EMMA.

148
00:06:21,507 --> 00:06:21,882
YOU OKAY?

149
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:24,384
YOU GOT THE NEWBORN
COLT LEGS THING GOING.

150
00:06:24,468 --> 00:06:26,136
WE'RE TRAINING
FOR CROSS-COUNTRY.

151
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,429
OH, WOW!

152
00:06:27,513 --> 00:06:29,556
THAT'S-THAT'S GREAT,
I HAD NO IDEA.

153
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,850
YEAH. THE THINGS YOU MISS
WHEN YOU LEAVE YOUR FAMILY.

154
00:06:40,567 --> 00:06:42,402
SO HOW'RE THINGS
AT JOEY'S?

155
00:06:42,486 --> 00:06:43,904
GOOD. OKAY.

156
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:46,323
NOT TOO BAD.

157
00:06:46,949 --> 00:06:48,992
TERRIBLE, ACTUALLY.

158
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,245
(EXHALES)
I MISS YOU GUYS.

159
00:06:52,329 --> 00:06:53,330
HAVE YOU TRIED
TELLING MOM THAT?

160
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:55,499
OH, I WOULD
BUT THAT WOULD INVOLVE

161
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:57,459
HER ACTUALLY RETURNING
MY PHONE CALLS.

162
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,587
SO WHY DON'T YOU TELL HER
IN PERSON?

163
00:07:00,671 --> 00:07:01,463
COME OVER TONIGHT.

164
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:02,631
THINK YOUR MOM
WOULD LIKE THAT?

165
00:07:02,714 --> 00:07:04,424
MAYBE IF YOU MADE US DINNER
LIKE YOU USED TO?

166
00:07:06,802 --> 00:07:07,177
EMMA!

167
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:11,723
YOU ARE A GENIUS!

168
00:07:28,532 --> 00:07:30,701
NOW THIS I COULD
GET USED TO.

169
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:33,328
WHAT'S THE AH...
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

170
00:07:33,412 --> 00:07:35,956
YOU HAVE A SURPRISE GUEST
FOR DINNER.

171
00:07:36,039 --> 00:07:38,792
A GUEST CHEF ACTUALLY.

172
00:07:38,876 --> 00:07:39,334
SNAKE.

173
00:07:39,418 --> 00:07:42,045
EMMA?
TELL ME YOU DIDN'T.

174
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,630
WHAT, I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE

175
00:07:43,714 --> 00:07:45,048
A NICE HOME-COOKED MEAL,
FOR ONCE.

176
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:46,758
(KNOCK AT THE DOOR)
I'LL GET IT!

177
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:52,097
SIMPSON:
DUNH-NA-NA-NAH!

178
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:55,726
ONE ORDER
OF VEGGIE MOUSSAKA.

179
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:56,977
EMMA'S OOEY-GOOEY
FAVOURITE.

180
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,354
ACTUALLY UM,

181
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:01,148
MANNY AND I ARE GONNA GO
FOR A WALK.

182
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,065
NO, GIRLS,

183
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:03,901
STAY.

184
00:08:04,526 --> 00:08:07,696
WHY DON'T YOU TWO
SET THE TABLE.

185
00:08:17,748 --> 00:08:19,666
(SNIFFS)
OH MY GOD, RICOTTA!

186
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,001
CREAM AND BUTTER
AND EVERYTHING ELSE

187
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:22,544
THAT I SEE IN MY DREAMS.

188
00:08:22,628 --> 00:08:23,587
WE HAVEN'T STARVED
FOR TWO DAYS

189
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:25,589
JUST TO RUIN IT IN
10 MINUTES OF GLUTTONY.

190
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:27,132
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

191
00:08:27,216 --> 00:08:29,218
WE SIT AT THE TABLE
WITH MOM AND ARCHIE

192
00:08:29,301 --> 00:08:30,052
AND TRY TO MAKE THEM HAPPY.

193
00:08:30,135 --> 00:08:31,762
AND THE FOOD WE JUST PUSH
AROUND YOUR PLATES.

194
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:34,723
(WATER DRIPS)

195
00:08:43,899 --> 00:08:47,069
KITCHEN FAUCET'S
STILL LEAKING, HUH?

196
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:48,654
I SHOULD GET MY WRENCH
AND UH...

197
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:50,739
IT'S FINE,
ARCHIE.

198
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:54,576
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH WATER
YOU'RE WASTING?

199
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,702
MY WRENCH IS DOWNSTAIRS-

200
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:57,621
JUST LEAVE IT!
PLEASE.

201
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,377
THIS MOUSSAKA
IS AMAZING.

202
00:09:06,964 --> 00:09:08,507
EMMA, I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
TOUCH YOURS.

203
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,092
EMMA:
SURE I HAVE.

204
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:13,470
YOUR COOKING IS SOMETHING
WE'VE REALLY MISSED AROUND HERE.

205
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:17,015
SIMPSON:
WELL, I MISS COOKING
FOR YOU GUYS.

206
00:09:17,099 --> 00:09:19,017
I MISS A LOT OF THINGS.

207
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:23,188
SITTING HERE AT THIS TABLE,

208
00:09:23,272 --> 00:09:26,358
I REALIZE THAT
THIS IS WHERE I BELONG,

209
00:09:26,441 --> 00:09:28,277
AND I NEVER SHOULD'VE LEFT.

210
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:30,028
YOU DIDN'T LEAVE,
SNAKE.

211
00:09:30,112 --> 00:09:31,321
I KICKED YOU OUT.

212
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:33,490
REMEMBER?

213
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:38,704
IT'S BEEN LONG ENOUGH, SPIKE.
AND I...

214
00:09:38,787 --> 00:09:39,705
I THINK I'VE LEARNED
MY LESSON.

215
00:09:40,706 --> 00:09:41,915
I'M READY TO COME HOME.

216
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:43,792
OH, AND THAT'S
YOUR DECISION TO MAKE?

217
00:09:43,876 --> 00:09:45,002
SIMPSON:
NO, IT'S OUR DECISION

218
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:46,086
BUT YES,
I HAVE A SAY IN IT.

219
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:47,504
YOU HAD YOUR SAY

220
00:09:47,588 --> 00:09:50,090
AND IT INVOLVED
ANOTHER WOMAN!

221
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:52,509
GIRLS...

222
00:09:52,593 --> 00:09:54,011
I THINK YOU NEED
TO GO TO YOUR ROOM.

223
00:10:03,187 --> 00:10:04,771
SIMPSON:
SPIKE, I CAME OVER HERE
WITH A PEACE OFFERING

224
00:10:04,855 --> 00:10:05,939
AND THIS IS WHAT I GET.

225
00:10:06,023 --> 00:10:07,232
SPIKE:
YOU THINK A PAN OF MOUSSAKA

226
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:08,775
IS GONNA MAKE EVERYTHING
BETTER?!

227
00:10:08,859 --> 00:10:09,610
SIMPSON:
NO, I DON'T!

228
00:10:09,693 --> 00:10:11,320
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD TRY
TO BE CIVILIZED-

229
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:14,072
FIGHTING.
ONLY FIGHTING.

230
00:10:14,156 --> 00:10:16,283
FIGHTING'S A START,
RIGHT?

231
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,577
IT'S BETTER THAN
NOT TALKING AT ALL.

232
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:19,119
I GUESS.

233
00:10:19,203 --> 00:10:20,204
SPIKE:
FINE! GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!

234
00:10:20,287 --> 00:10:20,954
I JUST WISH I KNEW

235
00:10:21,038 --> 00:10:21,788
HOW IT WAS GONNA
TURN OUT.

236
00:10:21,872 --> 00:10:23,624
I HATE NOT KNOWING
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

237
00:10:23,707 --> 00:10:24,416
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

238
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:26,210
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

239
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:27,711
I AM GOING TO EXPLODE

240
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:30,422
FROM ALL THAT OOEY-GOOEY
MOUSSAKEEY.

241
00:10:30,506 --> 00:10:31,840
I WISH I WOULD EXPLODE.

242
00:10:32,883 --> 00:10:33,926
WE COULD TRY AND RUN IT OFF.

243
00:10:34,009 --> 00:10:36,136
IT'LL ONLY TAKE
OH, SIX HOURS.

244
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:38,222
